content.text:
I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Here is my detailed plan.

---

## Approach: View Stash with LRU Eviction

### Philosophy

Don't destroy what you'll need again in 5 seconds. Park the Chromium process off-screen and keep a cap so memory stays bounded. The TerminalPanel already proves this pattern works in this codebase -- apply the same idea one layer down at the Electron main process level, where the real cost lives.

### The Core Problem

On workspace switch, `BrowserPanel.tsx` lines 209-216 call `hide()` then `close()` on every tab's native `WebContentsView`. `close()` calls `webContents.destroy()`, which kills the Chromium renderer process. The JS runtime, DOM, cookies, WebSocket connections, service workers -- all gone. When the user switches back, `hydratePersistedTab` generates a **new** webview label, creates a **new** `WebContentsView` from scratch, and reloads the URL cold. An agent actively testing a localhost app loses its entire session state.

### The Key Insight

The Electron main process `views` Map already stores `WebContentsView` instances keyed by label. The problem is the renderer generates a new random label on every hydration (`ws-${workspaceId.slice(0,8)}-tab-${Date.now()}-${rand}`), so there's no way to reconnect to an existing view. The fix is to make labels **stable per tab ID** and add a "stash/unstash" protocol to the main process that hides views without destroying them.

### Detailed Implementation Plan

#### 1. Electron Main Process: `browser-views.ts`

**New data structure** -- alongside the existing `views` Map, add a stashed-views Map and an LRU eviction tracker:

```typescript
// Existing
const views = new Map<string, WebContentsView>();
const viewBounds = new Map<string, Electron.Rectangle>();

// New: stashed views are hidden + removed from contentView, but NOT destroyed
const stashedViews = new Map<string, WebContentsView>();

// LRU tracking: ordered set of workspace IDs, most-recently-used at end.
// When total stashed views exceed the cap, evict the oldest workspace's views.
const MAX_STASHED_WORKSPACES = 3;
const workspaceLruOrder: string[] = []; // workspace IDs in LRU order
const workspaceViewLabels = new Map<string, Set<string>>(); // workspaceId -> set of labels
```

**New IPC handler: `stash_browser_workspace`** -- called instead of close on workspace switch:

```typescript
ipcMain.handle(
  "stash_browser_workspace",
  (_e, { workspaceId, labels }: { workspaceId: string; labels: string[] }) => {
    const mainWindow = BrowserWindow.getAllWindows()[0];
    if (!mainWindow) return;

    for (const label of labels) {
      const view = views.get(label);
      if (!view) continue;

      // Save bounds, remove from window, hide
      viewBounds.set(label, view.getBounds());
      mainWindow.contentView.removeChildView(view);
      view.setVisible(false);

      // Move from active to stashed
      views.delete(label);
      stashedViews.set(label, view);
    }

    // Track workspace -> labels mapping
    workspaceViewLabels.set(workspaceId, new Set(labels));

    // Update LRU order
    const idx = workspaceLruOrder.indexOf(workspaceId);
    if (idx !== -1) workspaceLruOrder.splice(idx, 1);
    workspaceLruOrder.push(workspaceId);

    // Evict oldest workspace if over cap
    while (workspaceLruOrder.length > MAX_STASHED_WORKSPACES + 1) {
      const evictId = workspaceLruOrder.shift()!;
      const evictLabels = workspaceViewLabels.get(evictId);
      if (evictLabels) {
        for (const label of evictLabels) {
          const evictView = stashedViews.get(label);
          if (evictView) {
            (evictView.webContents as any).destroy?.();
            stashedViews.delete(label);
            viewBounds.delete(label);
          }
        }
        workspaceViewLabels.delete(evictId);
      }
    }
  }
);
```

**New IPC handler: `unstash_browser_webview`** -- restores a stashed view without recreating it:

```typescript
ipcMain.handle(
  "unstash_browser_webview",
  (_e, { label, x, y, width, height }: { label: string; x: number; y: number; width: number; height: number }) => {
    const view = stashedViews.get(label);
    if (!view) return false; // caller should fall back to create_browser_webview

    const mainWindow = BrowserWindow.getAllWindows()[0];
    if (!mainWindow) return false;

    stashedViews.delete(label);
    views.set(label, view);

    const zoomFactor = mainWindow.webContents.getZoomFactor();
    const bounds = {
      x: Math.round(x * zoomFactor),
      y: Math.round(y * zoomFactor),
      width: Math.round(Math.max(width * zoomFactor, 100)),
      height: Math.round(Math.max(height * zoomFactor, 100)),
    };

    view.setBounds(bounds);
    mainWindow.contentView.addChildView(view);
    view.setVisible(true);
    viewBounds.set(label, bounds);

    return true; // restored successfully
  }
);
```

