## Plan: View Stash and Restore

### Philosophy Statement

"Don't destroy what you'll need again. Park the view, don't rebuild it."

Instead of destroying and recreating Chromium renderer processes on every workspace switch, we hide existing `WebContentsView` instances (remove from window hierarchy, `setVisible(false)`) and restore them when the user returns. The URL-only localStorage persistence becomes a fallback for cold starts, not the primary mechanism.

---

### Detailed Implementation Plan

The change is a two-layer stash: (1) the Electron main process learns to "park" and "unpark" views by workspace, and (2) the renderer stops destroying webviews on workspace switch and instead tells the main process to park them.

---

#### Data Structure: Workspace-scoped view registry (main process)

The flat `Map<string, WebContentsView>` stays as-is for label-based lookup. A second index groups labels by workspace, enabling bulk park/unpark operations.

```typescript
// browser-views.ts — new state alongside existing `views` Map

/** Maps workspaceId → Set of webview labels belonging to that workspace */
const workspaceViews = new Map<string, Set<string>>();

/** Labels that are currently parked (hidden + removed from window hierarchy) */
const parkedLabels = new Set<string>();
```

Key invariant: a label is always in `views` if the underlying `WebContentsView` exists (parked or not). `parkedLabels` tracks which ones are detached from the window hierarchy.

---

#### New IPC Handlers (main process)

**`park_workspace_views`** -- Hides and detaches all views for a workspace without destroying them.

```typescript
ipcMain.handle(
  "park_workspace_views",
  (_e, { workspaceId }: { workspaceId: string }) => {
    const mainWindow = BrowserWindow.getAllWindows()[0];
    const labels = workspaceViews.get(workspaceId);
    if (!mainWindow || !labels) return { parkedCount: 0 };

    let parkedCount = 0;
    for (const label of labels) {
      const view = views.get(label);
      if (!view) continue;
      // Save bounds before detaching
      viewBounds.set(label, view.getBounds());
      view.setVisible(false);
      mainWindow.contentView.removeChildView(view);
      parkedLabels.add(label);
      parkedCount++;
    }
    return { parkedCount };
  }
);
```

**`unpark_workspace_views`** -- Re-attaches all parked views for a workspace (hidden). The renderer will then show the active tab's view via the existing `show_browser_webview` handler.

```typescript
ipcMain.handle(
  "unpark_workspace_views",
  (_e, { workspaceId }: { workspaceId: string }) => {
    const mainWindow = BrowserWindow.getAllWindows()[0];
    const labels = workspaceViews.get(workspaceId);
    if (!mainWindow || !labels) return { labels: [] };

    const restored: string[] = [];
    for (const label of labels) {
      const view = views.get(label);
      if (!view || !parkedLabels.has(label)) continue;
      // Re-add to window hierarchy but keep hidden
      // BrowserTab's visibility effect will show the active one
      mainWindow.contentView.addChildView(view);
      view.setVisible(false);
      const savedBounds = viewBounds.get(label);
      if (savedBounds) view.setBounds(savedBounds);
      parkedLabels.delete(label);
      restored.push(label);
    }
    return { labels: restored };
  }
);
```

**`get_workspace_view_labels`** -- Returns which labels exist for a workspace (lets the renderer know if it can restore or must create).

```typescript
ipcMain.handle(
  "get_workspace_view_labels",
  (_e, { workspaceId }: { workspaceId: string }) => {
    const labels = workspaceViews.get(workspaceId);
    if (!labels) return [];
    // Only return labels whose WebContentsView still exists and is not destroyed
    return [...labels].filter((l) => views.has(l));
  }
);
```

**Modify `create_browser_webview`** -- Register the label in `workspaceViews` when a view is created. The workspace ID is extracted from the label convention (`ws-{id8}-tab-...`).

```typescript
// Inside create_browser_webview handler, after views.set(label, view):
const wsMatch = label.match(/^ws-([a-f0-9]{8})-tab-/);
if (wsMatch) {
  const wsId = wsMatch[1];
  if (!workspaceViews.has(wsId)) workspaceViews.set(wsId, new Set());
  workspaceViews.get(wsId)!.add(label);
}
```

**Modify `close_browser_webview`** -- Clean up from `workspaceViews` and `parkedLabels`.

```typescript
// Inside close_browser_webview handler, before views.delete(label):
parkedLabels.delete(label);
for (const [, labelSet] of workspaceViews) {
  labelSet.delete(label);
}
```

**Modify `destroyAllBrowserViews`** -- Clear the new data structures.

```typescript
export function destroyAllBrowserViews(): void {
  // existing cleanup...
  workspaceViews.clear();
  parkedLabels.clear();
}
```

