#### Memory Pressure: LRU Eviction

Parked views consume ~50-100MB each. With 10 workspaces each having 2 tabs, that is 1-2GB. We need an eviction policy.

Add a constant and eviction logic in `browser-views.ts`:

```typescript
const MAX_PARKED_VIEWS = 10; // configurable later

function evictOldestParkedWorkspace(): void {
  // workspaceViews iteration order is insertion order (Map)
  // Oldest workspace that has all labels parked gets evicted first
  for (const [wsId, labels] of workspaceViews) {
    const allParked = [...labels].every((l) => parkedLabels.has(l));
    if (!allParked) continue;

    const mainWindow = BrowserWindow.getAllWindows()[0];
    for (const label of labels) {
      const view = views.get(label);
      if (view) {
        if (mainWindow) mainWindow.contentView.removeChildView(view);
        (view.webContents as any).destroy?.();
        views.delete(label);
        viewBounds.delete(label);
        parkedLabels.delete(label);
      }
    }
    workspaceViews.delete(wsId);
    return; // evict one workspace at a time
  }
}
```

Called inside `park_workspace_views` after parking:

