# Plan: Park & Recall

## Philosophy Statement

Don't destroy what you can hide. The smallest step is to stop calling `close()` on workspace switch and instead `removeChildView()` + `setVisible(false)`, keeping the `WebContentsView` alive in memory. When the user returns, re-attach the existing view instead of creating a new one.

## Current Problem (Precise)

The workspace switch flow in `BrowserPanel.tsx` (lines 189-247) does this:

1. `hide(label)` -- sets view invisible
2. `close(label)` -- calls `removeChildView()` + `webContents.destroy()` + deletes from Map
3. Hydrates new tabs with `hydratePersistedTab()` which generates **new random webviewLabels**
4. New `BrowserTab` mounts, calls `create_browser_webview` with new label, `loadURL()` from scratch

The Chromium renderer process is destroyed. JS runtime, DOM tree, cookies, WebSocket connections, IndexedDB state, scroll positions, form data -- all gone. The agent-server actively testing loses its browser context.

## Approach: Two-Tier View Map in Electron Main

The core idea: the Electron main process manages two Maps instead of one. Active views are attached to the window. Parked views are detached but alive.

### Data Structures (browser-views.ts)

```typescript
// Active views — attached to contentView, visible or hidden
const views = new Map<string, WebContentsView>();
const viewBounds = new Map<string, Electron.Rectangle>();

// NEW: Parked views — detached from contentView, alive in memory
// Key: webviewLabel, Value: { view, workspaceId, parkedAt }
interface ParkedView {
  view: WebContentsView;
  workspaceId: string;
  parkedAt: number; // Date.now() for TTL eviction
}
const parkedViews = new Map<string, ParkedView>();

// NEW: workspace → labels index (for fast "get all views for workspace X")
const workspaceViewIndex = new Map<string, Set<string>>();
```

### New IPC Handlers (browser-views.ts)

**1. `park_browser_webviews` -- park all views for a workspace**

```typescript
ipcMain.handle(
  "park_browser_webviews",
  (_e, { workspaceId }: { workspaceId: string }) => {
    const mainWindow = BrowserWindow.getAllWindows()[0];
    const labels = workspaceViewIndex.get(workspaceId);
    if (!labels || !mainWindow) return;

    for (const label of labels) {
      const view = views.get(label);
      if (!view) continue;

      // Save bounds before detaching
      viewBounds.set(label, view.getBounds());
      // Detach from window (stops rendering, frees compositor resources)
      mainWindow.contentView.removeChildView(view);
      view.setVisible(false);
      // Move to parked map
      views.delete(label);
      parkedViews.set(label, {
        view,
        workspaceId,
        parkedAt: Date.now(),
      });
    }
  }
);
```

**2. `recall_browser_webview` -- check if a parked view exists, re-attach it**

```typescript
ipcMain.handle(
  "recall_browser_webview",
  (
    _e,
    {
      label,
      x,
      y,
      width,
      height,
    }: {
      label: string;
      x: number;
      y: number;
      width: number;
      height: number;
    }
  ): { recalled: boolean; url: string | null } => {
    const mainWindow = BrowserWindow.getAllWindows()[0];
    const parked = parkedViews.get(label);
    if (!parked || !mainWindow) {
      return { recalled: false, url: null };
    }

    const { view } = parked;
    parkedViews.delete(label);

    // Re-attach to window
    const zoomFactor = mainWindow.webContents.getZoomFactor();
    const bounds = {
      x: Math.round(x * zoomFactor),
      y: Math.round(y * zoomFactor),
      width: Math.round(Math.max(width * zoomFactor, 100)),
      height: Math.round(Math.max(height * zoomFactor, 100)),
    };

    mainWindow.contentView.addChildView(view);
    view.setBounds(bounds);
    view.setVisible(false); // Start hidden, BrowserTab will show when ready
    views.set(label, view);

    return {
      recalled: true,
      url: view.webContents.getURL(),
    };
  }
);
```

**3. `get_parked_views_for_workspace` -- query what's parked for a workspace**

```typescript
ipcMain.handle(
  "get_parked_views_for_workspace",
  (_e, { workspaceId }: { workspaceId: string }): Array<{ label: string; url: string; title: string }> => {
    const result: Array<{ label: string; url: string; title: string }> = [];
    for (const [label, parked] of parkedViews) {
      if (parked.workspaceId === workspaceId) {
        result.push({
          label,
          url: parked.view.webContents.getURL(),
          title: parked.view.webContents.getTitle(),
        });
      }
    }
    return result;
  }
);
```

